    <ResourceType>NumericalData</ResourceType>
    <ResourceHeader>
      <ResourceName>Magnetic Field Spectra in GSE (burst; up to 225 Hz)</ResourceName>
      <AlternateName>C4_CP_STA_CS_HBR</AlternateName>
      <ReleaseDate>2026-02-28T12:00:00</ReleaseDate>
      <RevisionHistory>
        <RevisionEvent>
          <ReleaseDate>2026-02-28T12:00:00</ReleaseDate>
          <Note>Initial release of metadata.</Note>
        </RevisionEvent>
      </RevisionHistory>
      <Description>This dataset contains calibrated Complex Spectra (CS) of the magnetic field measured by the STAFF
        magnetic waveform unit (STAFF-SC) from 0.1Hz to 225Hz with a resolution of 0.109866Hz x 9.10s,
        in High Bit Rate (HBR) mode on the Cluster C4 spacecraft.
        This product is given in Geocentric Solar Ecliptic (GSE) coordinate system.
        Data calibration is performed using a moving window of 4096 points in HBR mode.
        This value was chosen as the best compromise for routine production.
        For further details, please refer to the STAFF Calibration Report.</Description>
      <Acknowledgement>Please acknowledge the STAFF team and ESA Cluster Science Archive in any publication based upon use of this data. 
        Digital Object Identifier for the STAFF archive: doi.org/10.5270/esa-yrzyijm</Acknowledgement>
